Colombia Stocks: Bolsa de Valores, Canacol Energy, ETB

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-31T16:49:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/colombia-stocks-bolsa-de-valores-canacol-energy-etb.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:09 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.2 percent to 14,423.04, while the
Colcap Index was little changed at 1,738.05.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia (BVC)  SA, the operator of
the country’s main securities exchange, rose 1.4 percent to 43.5
pesos, a fourth-month high on an intraday basis, after trading
began yesterday across Colombian, Peruvian and Chilean bourses
in  Latin America ’s first international exchange integration.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  South America , rose 1.6 percent
to 2,275 pesos after it announced a partnership yesterday with
C&C Energia Ltd. for drilling three exploration wells in the
second half of the year.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota (ETB)  SA, the
state-run phone company serving Colombia’s capital, rose 3.1
percent to 700 pesos, the highest intraday since March 25. The
city is expected to present a proposal to the Bogota city
council as soon as this week to sell part of its majority stake
in the company, newspaper El Tiempo reported, citing sources it
didn’t identify. “There’s a lot of speculation the city will
sell its stake soon,” said Mauricio Restrepo del Toro, head of
research at brokerage Bolsa y Renta.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
